pwman is a nimble password manager written in pure POSIX shell [1].
pwman is composed of

  pwgen  -- create high quality random passwords
  pwget  -- get a password from the password store
  pwsort -- sort password stores alphabetically

  TODO: pwprint -- pretty print password stores.

Two of the above scripts (pwget and pwsort) act on a password store,
which is a plaintext file containing records in the following format:

  == example.com ==
  password
  username
  additional info.
  ...

  == example.com ==
  password
  username
  additional info.
  ...

Each line starting and ending with "==" begins a new record.  The two
lines following it contain the password and username respectively.
Additional lines are treated as comments.  Individual records are
separated by blank line.

[1]: Well, actually not that pure.  You might need some evil GNU tools!
